const sortedData = [...data].sort((a, b) => { switch(sortBy) { case 'sold': return b.sold - a.sold; case 'active': return b.active - a.active; case 'total': return b.total - a.total; case 'soldRatio': return b.soldRatio - a.soldRatio; default: return a.community.localeCompare(b.community); } }); const totalActive = data.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.active, 0); const totalSold = data.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.sold, 0); const pieData = [ { name: 'Active Listings', value: totalActive, color: '#c4963d' }, { name: 'Properties Sold', value: totalSold, color: '#2c3e50' } ];
